from nobody subject jerry berman on pseudonymou privacy hello all i think you all might like to see thi it a letter from jerry berman to david chaum from november of in response to information that mr chaum send to mr berman while i have to congratulate eff for it prompt response to the clipper chip announcement from the white house i think it important to recognize the philosophy of their executive director a explain below i agree that legal remedy be important but when press i prefer to retain the ability to use purely technical solution to preserve my privacy because they hold up under fire mr chaum ha consent to the publication of thi letter on the net i do work for nor be i a member of eff aclu or any similar organization but i do agree with them on a great many thing aristophane american civil liberty union washington office maryland avenue ne november washington dc national headquarters mr david chaum west street centre for mathematics and computer science new york ny box ab amsterdam norman dorsen president dear mr chaum ira glasser executive director eleanor holme norton chair national advisory council thank you for send me a most interest article a society of individual and organization that would expend the time and resource to use a series of pseudonym to avoid datum linkage do not in my opinion make big brother obsolete but act on the assumption that big brother be ever present i view ymy system a a form of societal paranoium a a matter of principle we be work to enact formal legal protection for individual privacy rather than rely on technical solution we want to assume a society of law which respect legal limit rather than a society that will disobey the law require citizen to depend on technical solution require a judical warrant for government interception of datum communication rather than encrypt all message on the assumption that regardles of the lawt the government will abuse it power and invade privacy a a matter of practicality i do not think ymy system offer much hope for privacy first the trend toward universal identifier be a movement generate by government or industry desire to keep track of all citizen a it be by citizen seek simplicity and convenience in all transaction at best ymy system would benefit the sophisticate and most would opt for simplicity the poor and the undereducated would never use or benefit from it finally where there a will there a way if government want to link datum basis it will by law require the disclosure of variou individual pseudonym use by citizen or prohibit it for datum basis which the government want to link since corporation make money by trade commercial list with one another they will never adopt the system or if it be adopt will use fine printn contract to permit sell variou code use by their customer to other firm the solution remain law policy and consensu about limit on government or corporate intrusion into area of individual autonomy technique can be use to enforce that consensu or to override it it can not be use a a substitute for such consensu sincerely your sig jerry j berman chief legislative counsel direrector aclu privacy technology project cc john shattuck 